We spoke about specific knowledge, we talked about accountability, we talked about leverage. The last skill that Naval talks about in his tweetstorm is judgment, where he says, that &amp;ldquo;Leverage is a force multiplier for your judgment.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Which universities should one apply to?</title><link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/which-universities-should-one-apply-to/</link><pubDate>Mon, 14 May 2007 00:51:30 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/which-universities-should-one-apply-to/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/which-universities-should-one-apply-to.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;
