&lt;h1 id="which-universities-should-one-apply-to"&gt;Which universities should one apply to?&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A college degree is not a sign that one is a finished product but an indication a person is prepared for life.
— Edward Malloy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Going to college is a major event in one&amp;rsquo;s education, but the choice of exactly which college to go to is not as critical as it is sometimes portrayed to be; usually, there will be several good choices that suit your specific strengths and weaknesses, and it is not absolutely necessary to secure the &amp;ldquo;best&amp;rdquo; choice for your undergraduate or graduate education. I would recommend a flexible attitude towards this decision; by focusing too much on one institution, you might overlook others which may in fact be a better fit for you.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>The Right Kind of Stubborn</title><link>https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_en/persistence/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_en/persistence/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_zh/persistence/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
